abstract: MASSACHUSETTS TEACHERS ASSOCIATION.-- The Annual meeting of this Association at New Bedford, on Monday and Tuesday of this week, was a rich treat to the friends of Education who had the pleasure of being present. Very able and interesting lectures were delivered by Mr. GOLDTHWAIT of Westfield, Mr. HOVT of Dover, N. H. and Prof. FELTON of Harvard College.

abstract: We now await the result of no less than three issues that have been made in regard to the Cuban flurry. The first and most important is that now pending between the Governments of the United States and of Old Spain; the next is between Mr. LAW and the Cuban officials; and the third is between this Government and Mr LAW.

abstract: The New-York Historical Society's Lectures have already been announced. The Committee in charge of the arrangements have deemed it advisable to effect a slight alteration in the programme. Instead of the issue of free tickets to the members of the Society, the rate of admission will be lowered to a uniform standard of five dollars for the Course.
